method.name: emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config
method.description: Used to configure simulating subscriber lines behind an ANCP enabled Access Node.

description.text: Used to specify the action that the function will perform on the given ANCP Client session handle. Every mode except create, enable_all, and disable_all requires a valid AN Subscriber Line Pool handle. Modes create, enable_all, and disable_all will perform on any given ANCP Client handle

choice.choiceText: ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is mandatory. This mode will create a DSL Profile and DSL Resync profile and add it to the profiles used by the ANCP Client. If an identical profile already exists it will be used instead of creating a new one

handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config is mandatory. All the TLVs will be removed from this profile and new ones will be added according to the procedure parameters. In this case the parameters will not accept lists (single values only)
handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config is mandatory. The DSL Profile specified with -handle will be removed

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config and handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config are mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will use the DSL Profile specified with -handle parameter.

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config and handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config are mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will stop using the DSL Profile specified with -handle parameter
ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will use all DSL Profiles available
ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will not use any DSL Profiles

restriction.value: create modify delete enable disable enable_all disable_all

description.text: Enable Actual-Net-Data-Rate-Downstream TLV
Used to set emulated actual DSL sync rate (kbps) downstream. It may be a list of rate values. Default: None Dependencies: maximum 63 digits

Step for actual_rate_downstream. The DSL TLV Resync Profile will be configured as trend starting from actual_rate_downstream with a step of actual_rate_downstream_step and ending at -actual_rate_downstream_end.
Enable Actual-Net-Data-Rate-Upstream TLV
Used to set emulated actual DSL sync rate (kbps) upstream. It may be a list of rate values. Default: None Dependencies: maximum 63 digits

Step for actual_rate_upstream. The DSL TLV Resync Profile will be configured as trend starting from actual_rate_upstream with a step of actual_rate_upstream_step and ending at actual_rate_upstream_end.

This parameter is used to specify the ANCP Client session handle on which ANCP Subscriber Line Pool will be added. This handle is returned by procedure emulation_ancp_config. May be a list, in which case all the handles are configured with the same parameters. Default: None Dependencies: None
Used to set circuit id. May be a list, needs to have the same length as ancp_client_handle. Dependencies: None
Type of Access Loop Technology
Enable DSL Type TLV
Used to set the type of DSL transmission system in use. Dependencies: maximum 63 digits

restriction.value: adsl1 adsl2 adsl2_plus vdsl1 vdsl2 sdsl unknown

description.text: Enable PON Type TLV
PON Type value for PON Type TLV

restriction.value: gpon xgpon1 twdmpon xgspon wdmpon other

description.text: Used to modify, enable, disable or delete AN Subscriber Line Pool handle. This handle is returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config procedure. Default: None Dependencies: None
Enable Access-Loop-Remote-ID TLV

Used to set remote id. This parameter is also use to enable Remote Id option. Hence, if and only if the switch remote_id is specified, Remote Id option will be enabled. Dependencies: maximum 63 digits
Inner VLAN ID for vlan_allocation_model N_1 and 1_1 VLAN mapping in Access-Aggregation-Circuit-ID-Binary TLV
Step for customer_vlan_id
Percentage for variation of Actual Net Data Rate Downstream TLV value when sending port-up messages in flapping behavior
Enable a flapping profile

Send Port-Up messages, one message every 'Flap Interval' seconds
Disable flapping, and Send Port-Up if line state is SILENT

description.text: Outer VLAN ID for vlan_allocation_model 1_1 VLAN mapping in Access-Aggregation-Circuit-ID-Binary TLV
Step for service_vlan_id
Interval in milliseconds to wait after sending port-down message when flapping is enabled
Interval in milliseconds to wait after sending port-up message when flapping is enabled
Number of subscriber lines to create per Access Node
Percentage for variation of Actual Net Data Rate Upstream TLV value when sending port-up messages in flapping behavior
Access-Aggregation-Circuit-ID-Binary TLV disable, enable N:1 vlan allocation model or 1:1 vlan allocation model

returnValue.value: A list containing the ancp subscriber lines protocol stack handles that were added by the command (if any).
When status is failure, contains more information.
<ancp_subscriber_lines_handle> Please note that this key will be omitted if the current session or command were run with -return_detailed_handles 0.

notes.note: 1) Unsupported parameters or unsupported parameter options will be silently ignored. If the current session or command was run with -return_detailed_handles 0 the following keys will be omitted from the command response: handle
